        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer416948145" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer881803160298304395">I&apos;m struggling to decide between 3 &amp; 4 stars for this, so I&apos;ll go with 3.5 :)<br/><br/>I enjoyed the story a lot, it was almost un-putdownable. I was completely intrigued and wanted to find out what was going to happen because I&apos;ve never read a book about angels or heaven or anything like that, so the theme of The Bringer was completely new to me. What I like most was Lucyna &amp; Jame&apos;s connection and just the feeling of hope I got from them. I wish there had been more of them actually together, it seemed li</span>
  <span id="freeText881803160298304395" style="display:none">I'm struggling to decide between 3 &amp; 4 stars for this, so I'll go with 3.5 :)<br /><br />I enjoyed the story a lot, it was almost un-putdownable. I was completely intrigued and wanted to find out what was going to happen because I've never read a book about angels or heaven or anything like that, so the theme of The Bringer was completely new to me. What I like most was Lucyna &amp; Jame's connection and just the feeling of hope I got from them. I wish there had been more of them actually together, it seemed like there was one conflict after another after another. That being said, I still liked it a lot and was satisfied that <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[ Luce &amp; James atleast got to be together in the end could spend the rest of their lives (&amp; after I'm assuming) together (btw, does a HEA <i> really</i> count as a spoiler? I'm not sure, so just to be safe...) <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> <br /><br />The suspense was good and it kept me guessing the whole time, which was fun because I can usually guess the twists in books from the beginning. Overall very enjoyable read - I'll definitely continue to read Samantha Towle's work in the future. </span>
  <a data-text-id="881803160298304395" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
